The text discusses the Women's Empowerment in Livestock Index (WELI), which measures women's empowerment in livestock-related livelihoods. 

It explains how WELI assesses the impact of livestock interventions on women's empowerment, aiming to enhance their opportunities and promote gender equity while improving household livelihoods and nutrition.

The text discusses the development of drought- and heat-resilient bean varieties in Africa through collaborative breeding networks. It highlights the importance of common beans as a staple food and the efforts of organizations like CIAT and PABRA to improve bean varieties based on farmer feedback and market demands.

This summary emphasizes the focus on enhancing agricultural resilience and nutrition through genetic innovation in bean breeding.
